answer:
A variable argument function or variadic function is written with mandatory fixed arguments followed by ellipsis (...). Ellipsis statnds for variable number of arguments of any type.

Such a function needs at least one fixed arguement.

The header file to be included  here is stdarg.h  An object of type va_list must be defined. Macros va_start,va_arg and va_end defined in this header file, are used for accessing the variable arguments.

e.g.

void print_numbers(float b,int a,...)
{
va_list list1;
int m;
double n;
va_start(list1,a);/* a is last fixed argument*/
m = va_arg(list1,int);
n = va_arg(list1,double);
va_end(list1;);
}

va_start should specify the variable arg list macro and the last fixed argument. This initializes the variable list.

va_arg extracts one argument at a time. It should specify variable arg list and the data type of argument to be  extracted. The type should be either int or double. All other types will be promoted to these two types.

va_end finalizes the list.

